⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Epona
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦Epona:ZEL:984a27⟧

WHO   — Epona — the Steed
WHAT  — The Hero's horse — a living beast and a faithful friend, the steady mount that bears Link from one age's adventure to the next, calmed and called by Epona's Song.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a hero alone covers little ground, and a friend with four swift legs covers a kingdom; because trust is earned between rider and mount; because she comes when she is called, and a bond, once made, does not break.
HOW   — By swift hooves over Hyrule Field, by the leap of a fence and the dash through danger; by the carrot's spur and, above all, by the song — Epona's Song, the melody learned in childhood that calls her near.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I come when the song is played — four swift hooves and a faithful heart, to carry the Hero across the land.

